About Me

My name is Alexander Lehnbom, and I'm a 28-year-old developer originally from Gävle, Sweden. I have spent a significant portion of my life in Toronto, Canada, and am passionate about technology and programming. My educational background includes studying programming at IT-Högskolan, web development at Johns Hopkins University, and currently, I am expanding my skills in front-end development at Sundsgarden. Throughout my career, I have gained diverse work experience, including roles as a product specialist and in various tech support positions. As I continue to focus on my front-end development studies at Sundsgarden, I am committed to excelling in the field and contributing to the success of my future employer.

Travel has been an essential aspect of my life, as I have explored various parts of the world, such as Europe, India, South America, and Southeast Asia. I have had the unique opportunity to work remotely during my adventures, which has provided me with valuable insights into different cultures and perspectives. When I'm not working on my laptop, I enjoy staying active by running and training. I firmly believe that hard work and stepping outside one's comfort zone are the keys to personal growth. This belief has fueled my motivation to continually develop my skills and adapt to new challenges. As I look toward the future, my ambition is to build a successful career as a developer. I am confident that with my strong work ethic, dedication to learning, and love for exploration, I can make a meaningful impact in the world of technology and be an invaluable asset to any employer.

); } export default AboutPage;
